Pour @water{240%ml} (double for 4p) into a large #pot. Stir in the @vegetable stock{1%sachet} and bring to the boil.

Chop the @sweet potato{300%grams} into 2cm chunks (peeling optional).

Roughly chop the @parsley{5%grams} (stalks and all).

Drain and rinse the @lentils{1%pack} in a #sieve.

Zest and cut the @lime{1} into wedges.

> TIP: If you're in a hurry you can boil the water in your kettle.

Once the water is boiling, stir in the @bulgur wheat{120%grams} then bring back up to the boil.

Simmer for ~{1%minute} then pop a #lid on the pot and remove from the heat.

Leave to the side for ~{12-15%minutes} or until ready to serve.

Place a large pan over high heat with a generous drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

When hot, add the sweet potato and fry for ~{4-5%minutes}, stirring occasionally.

Lower the heat to medium-high then add the @ras-el-Hanout{1%sachet}, @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Cook for ~{1%minute}.

Add the sweet potato, @chopped tomato with onion & garlic{1%pack}, lentils, @coconut milk{1%pack}, @peanut butter{1%sachet} and @water{75%ml} (double for 4p) to a large #pot.

Bring to a boil, then cover and simmer for ~{10-12%minutes}.

Fluff up the bulgur with a #fork.

Stir through the lime zest and half the parsley.

Divide the stew between bowls.

Top with @peanuts{20%grams}, lime wedges and remaining parsley.